      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 11.86,
      "end": 15.7,
      "text": "Recorded by Christine Doer, the known as Assa, Florida.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.18,
      "end": 18.02,
      "text": "Asop's Fables",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 19.04,
      "end": 19.82,
      "text": "The Two Pots",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 20.54,
      "end": 27.16,
      "text": "Two Pots, one of earthenware, and the other of brass, were carried away down a river",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 27.16,
      "end": 27.84,
      "text": "in flood.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 28.7,
      "end": 33.98,
      "text": "The brazen pot urged his companion to keep close by his side, and he would protect him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 34.9,
      "end": 38.56,
      "text": "The other thanked him, but begged him not to come near him on any account.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 39.34,
      "end": 42.54,
      "text": "For that, he said, is just what I am most afraid of.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 43.3,
      "end": 46.2,
      "text": "One touch from you, and I should be broken in pieces.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 47.94,
      "end": 50.1,
      "text": "Equals make the best friends.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 52.08,
      "end": 54.12,
      "text": "End of the Two Pots",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
